HEADWORD: Eudialyte
<hw>Eu*di"a*lyte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>e'y^</grk> well, easily + <?/ to dissolve. So called because easily
dissolvable in acids.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a
brownish red color and vitreous luster, consisting chiefly of the
silicates of iron, zirconia, and lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

